here and it has given me something to think about. Yes I am a very emotional person, I cant always help that, and maybe I went a little over what I should have. But it is the way I am that keeps me loved by the few people that have gotten to know me and keeps me from ever yelling at another person or ever acting like a jerk in /ooc /shouts or message boards.<br>
<br>
XP just seemed sooo important to getting ahead. I had felt that I did out grow my old guild so I left to be on my own (which was recently). I've just wanted to get into the same guild as my rl friends (been trying for a year, always 1-2 steps behind). Though by doing so, the only good friends I have are my old guildies, rl's, 1-2 people from rl's guild, and 1-2 others.<br>
<br>
But... I do agree with what some have said that may have seemed negative. I was never one to pull a group together to go hunt, I've always given a friend that task or had rl's call me when a group could be made. I still don't see myself as a leader but its worthe the try. And I will have try to abandon some of my shyness to look into that making friends with strangers idea =).<br>
<br>
I stay away from soloing. I think that soloing has changed since Luclin+ mobs have had increased hp. Too much soloing has just felt lonely and I very much enjoy the company of others. With C3, PoD yard trash gives me a hard enough time. It will take me an entire mana bar and sometimes a mid harvest to kill a diseased rat, just to get 1% aaxp, or less than a twitch of regular xp. (Maybe I'm not doing things right, but no one taught me to solo, something I picked up on my own. I never had a wizard friend that was higher than myself)<br>
<br>
It's not the time to be complaining about bad xp or feeling that the game owes me something nor did I mean my post to sound that way. I had like to know how other wizards get through the game and now I have a few ideas of just how to do it better than I was handling it.<br>
<br>
Thanks all for posting, and thank you Andrael for your kind words.<br>
<br>
